One of Motor's messiest problems is how to support Futures alongside its original callback-based API:
{noformat}
# Old-fashioned:
def callback(result, error):
    if error:
        print(error)
    else:
        print(result)

def func():
    motor_client.db.collection.insert_one({'_id': 1}, callback=callback)

# Modern:
@gen.coroutine
def func():
    result = yield motor_client.db.collection.insert_one({'_id': 1})

# Contemporary:
async def func():
    result = await motor_client.db.collection.insert_one({'_id': 1})
{noformat}
After [a discussion with Tornado's maintainer|https://groups.google.com/d/topic/python-tornado/Ki8t6MVI_K8/discussion] I've decided that Motor 2.0 should drop the old-fashioned callback interface.

